  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Iowa through FY2026 to date total $1.2B across 16,435 awards, with an average award size of $72.6K and year-over-year change down 66.8%. Obligations peaked and varied across recent fiscal years: $2.5B in FY21, $2.7B in FY22, $3.4B in FY23, $3B in FY24, $3.6B in FY25, and $1.2B in FY26. The Department of Defense is the dominant buyer in FY2026 to date with $767M in obligations, followed by Department of the Treasury at $158M and Department of Agriculture at $95.7M. Large vendor receipts are concentrated: ROCKWELL COLLINS, INC. recorded $288M and DATA LINK SOLUTIONS LLC recorded $248M; PMX INDUSTRIES, INC. reported $103M. Manufacturing and engineering-related NAICS categories lead spending, including Other Communications Equipment Manufacturing at $256M and Copper Rolling, Drawing, Extruding, and Alloying at $103M. Other significant categories include Engineering Services at $96.4M and Radio and Television Broadcasting and Wireless Communications Equipment Manufacturing at $98.9M. These figures are fiscal year to date and current-year totals are partial.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How have annual obligations changed recently?",
        "body": "Obligations rose from $2.5B in FY21 to $3.4B in FY23, then moved to $3B in FY24 and $3.6B in FY25 before falling to $1.2B in FY26. Year-over-year change is down 66.8% for the current fiscal year to date."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which buyers and industries dominate FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense leads with $767M in obligations, followed by Department of the Treasury at $158M and Department of Agriculture at $95.7M. Top industries include Other Communications Equipment Manufacturing at $256M, Radio and Television Broadcasting and Wireless Communications Equipment Manufacturing at $98.9M, and Engineering Services at $96.4M."
      }
    ]
  },
